setAmountForRates

public void setAmountForRates(Amount amount)
for rates, the amount needs to be set without resetting the charge type. So call this one only in case of rates.

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - in case the method is called outside of a A- or D-rated context, that is: when the chargeType is not related to A- or D-rate.
